<dl id="n12146k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12146k">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12146k"> 146(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> council of &mdash; / declared <font face="wake">C</font> SP guilty</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le concile de Sardique (343-344) d&eacute;clara saint Athanase innocent&hellip; Il est vrai qu&apos;au Concile de Rimini &hellip; vingt &eacute;v&ecirc;ques gaulois se laiss&egrave;rent ciconvenir par les raisonnements des h&eacute;r&eacute;tiques. De retour en Gaule, ils se ressaisirent et condemn&egrave;rent l&apos;h&eacute;r&eacute;sie. <br><font color="green">[144: The Council of Sardica (343-344) declared St Athanasius innocent &hellip; It is true that at the Council of Rimini &hellip; twenty Gallic bishops allowed themselves to be deceived by the specious arguments of the heretics. But on their return to Gaul, they changed their opinion and condemned the heresy.]</font> <small> Riguet, Abb&eacute; <a name="RTSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RTSP"><cite title="source">Saint Patrice</cite></a> (1911) 171</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
